## Source

`BytePort` is the Rust-based high-throughput message-bus repo owned
by `kooshapari`. It is an active, public repo with healthy CI and
recent development activity.

`_bp_status_decoded.md` and `_byteport_audit_decoded.md` confirm
the repo is healthy:

- Default branch: `main`.
- Last commit: 2026-06-22.
- CI: green.
- Rust migration: in flight (see
  `_bp_rust_migration_decoded.md`).

The repo contains:

- Core `byteport` crate (Rust).
- Internal modules being migrated from older TypeScript/Go
  implementations.
- CI surface: 4 reusable workflows, 2 SBOM pipelines.
- Documentation: `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/architecture.md`.

### Local filesystem presence

- `C:\Users\koosh\BytePort` — EXISTS, active.
- `gh api repos/KooshaPari/BytePort` — returns active repo metadata.
- `_bp_remotes_dated.txt` and `_bp_remotes.txt` confirm the
  upstream remote is `origin` pointing to
  `https://github.com/KooshaPari/BytePort`.

### Why this is in scope for absorption review

BytePort is in scope because it is the **source** for a Rust
migration landing in `phenotype-infra/packages/byteport-rust`. The
AFFIRM verdict here does not mean "do nothing"; it means
"continue the in-flight migration." The repo continues to exist,
and selected internal modules are absorbed into `phenotype-infra`
over time.

The verdict is therefore the AFFIRM-with-migration variant:
**repo is not deleted; absorption is partial and progressive.**

---

## Target

The target for absorption is **`phenotype-infra`**
(`C:\Users\koosh\phenotype-infra`), specifically the pending
`packages/byteport-rust` package.

Per `phenotype-infra-2026-06-23.md` (this session), `phenotype-infra`
is AFFIRM and absorbs the migration from `BytePort`. The absorption
path is **progressive module-by-module**, not a wholesale fork
merge.

### What is absorbed

- **`byteport-core`** (the core message-bus library).
- **`byteport-codec`** (the wire-codec crate).
- **`byteport-router`** (the routing module).
- Selected CLI tooling.

### What is NOT absorbed

- **`byteport-cli`** standalone binary — stays in `BytePort` repo as
  the public CLI entry point.
- **`byteport-bench/`** — stays in `BytePort` repo as the
  benchmarking harness.
- **`byteport-website/`** — stays in `BytePort` repo.

### Why phenotype-infra and not a fresh repo

Creating a new `byteport-rust-org` repo would violate ADR-008
(consolidation over proliferation) and ADR-039 (monorepo preference
for SDK-layer code). `phenotype-infra/packages/` is the designated
landing pad; `packages/byteport-rust` will be a sub-package once
the migration completes.

---

