## Restore-Command

```
# Restore not applicable - BytePort is active and not deleted.
# AFFIRM verdict means the repo continues in place.

# However, rollback of any specific migration PR is supported:
# If a migration PR is regretted, revert in phenotype-infra:
git -C C:\Users\koosh\phenotype-infra revert <migration-pr-sha>
git -C C:\Users\koosh\phenotype-infra push origin main

# BytePort-side rollback (e.g., bump back to previous crate version):
# Edit byteport-cli's Cargo.toml to depend on the pre-migration crate.
git -C C:\Users\koosh\BytePort checkout main
# (manual edit of Cargo.toml dependency pin)
git -C C:\Users\koosh\BytePort commit -am "revert: pin byteport-cli to <previous-version>"
git -C C:\Users\koosh\BytePort push origin main

# Disaster recovery (full BytePort reconstruction):
gh api repos/KooshaPari/BytePort  # confirm repo still exists
git clone https://github.com/KooshaPari/BytePort.git \
  C:\Users\koosh\BytePort-restored
```

**Restore posture:** Repo is active; no `git bundle` required for
disaster recovery (the upstream remote IS the recovery source).
Rollback of migration PRs is via `git revert` in either repo.
**Documented restore path:** `git clone` from
`https://github.com/KooshaPari/BytePort.git`, or `git revert` of
any regretted migration PR.

